rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Court

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Founded

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judges

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Jurisdiction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date (if any) that the court last occupied the courthouse. If the court occupied the courthouse multiple, non-contiguous times, then there should be a separate instance of the property for each of these times.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Courts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.criminal to the number of victims killed in crimes committed by the criminal.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an invention to the date that it was conceived.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all judgments. These are the decisions handed down by a judge or other, similar authority. This collection includes legal judgments as well as judgments handed down by other governing agents. For example, a sports organization can make judgments about the conduct of members and in some cases assess fines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judgement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.judgment to the number of hours of community service sentenced in the judgment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Community Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.judgment to the mso:time.event, which is the event that is the subject of the judgment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Crime

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.judicial_decision to the amount of money fined in the judgment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.judgment to the mso:event.agent that received the judgment, viz. the agent that was acquitted or found guilty.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judged Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.judgment to the mso:law.legal_case that the judgment concerns.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Case

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the courts where judges have presided, the role that they had there, and the time frame that they had the role.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judicial Tenure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the given judge first held the title in the given court. If the judge held the title or sat on the court multiple non-contiguous times, a separate instance of the property should be created for each of these times.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the given judge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the title of the given judge. Note that, in some jurisdictions, judges do not sit on specific courts, but rather have positions which determine the types of courts they may sit on.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Title

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the given judge last held the title in the given court. If the judge held the title or sat on the court multiple non-contiguous times, a separate instance of the property should be created for each of these times.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for titles held by judges, e.g. Barrister, Chief Justice, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judicial Title

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A law is any rule that has been enacted by a government, including approved legislation and decrees made by a head of state.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Law

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all law enforcement organizations. These are national, international, and local organizations concerned with preventing crime and enforcing the law.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Law Enforcement Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all law firms. Law firms are businesses containing one or more lawyers whose mission is to represent clients in legal matters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Law Firm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.law_firm to the number of lawyers the form has employed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Lawyers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.law_firm to the types of mso:law.legal_subject the firm practices.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type of Firm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A legal case is a legal action brought before a court of law.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal case

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a legal case to the court the case was immediately appealed from.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Appealed From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a legal case to the court the case was immediately appealed to.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Appealed To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a legal case to the time frame when arguments in the proceedings for the case were presented.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Argued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a legal case to an associate judge, i.e. a judge other than the chief judge, in the proceedings of the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Associate Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a legal case to the chief judge in the proceedings.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chief Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Legal cases that are referenced by the given case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Citations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a legal case to one of the judges who wrote a concurring opinion on the legal case's verdict.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Concurring Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a legal case to the court in which the case was heard.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Court

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a legal case to the date when a decision on the case was made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Decided

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:law.legal_case to the judge that wrote the case's decision.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Decision By

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a legal case to one of the judges who wrote a dissenting opinion on the legal case's verdict.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dissenting Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to its U.S. Supreme Court docket number.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Docket Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to a brief description of the case's central ruling.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holding

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a legal case to a judge who presided over the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: judges

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to the mso:law.judgment that was passed in the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judgment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to the mso:law.legislation that are citations to the constitutional and statutory provisions that were the primary basis for the decision. This property does not include all case law associated with the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Laws Applied

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to the mso:event.agent that is named as a litigant, either as a plantiff or defendant. More specific and other roles for mso:law.legal_cases may be expressed with mso:law.legal_case_party_relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Litigant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a mso:law.legal_case to its prior trials or appeals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prior Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to the general and brief description of the case's prior history. If possible, the structured property mso:law.legal_case.prior_action should be used instead.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prior History

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:law.legal_case to any related actions. Related actions are those that have a connection to the mso:law.legal_case, but fall outside of the mso:law.legal_case.prior_action and mso:law.legal_case.subsequent_action properties.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a legal case to a standard descriptor for the broad subject matter of the case, e.g. abortion, discrimination, taxation, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:law.legal_case to any subsequent actions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subsequent Action

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Proeprty relating an mso:law.legal_case to a general and brief description of the case's subsequent action. If possible, the structured property mso:law.legal_case.subsequent_action should be used instead.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subsequent History

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a legal case to a partial or complete transcript of the proceedings of the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Transcript

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_case to its citation in the United States Report, the official record of rulings, orders, and other case proceedings of the Supreme Court of the United States.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: US Reports Citation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the parties involved in a legal case and the roles that they held in the case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Case/Party Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the given legal case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Case

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the role of the given agent in the legal case, e.g. plaintiff, defendant, witness, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Role

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all legal documents. These are documents that are issued by an agent with legal authority and may grant a right, state a contractual relationship, or accomplish some other legal goal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Document

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_document to an mso:law.crime_type that is covered in the document.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Crime Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_document to the date the document was issued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Issued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legal_document to the agent that issued the document, a court, agency, or individual.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Issuer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A litigation role is a role that a party to a legal case can hold, such as plaintiff (claimant, petitioner, etc.) or defendant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Litigation Role

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or organization that provides some form of legal counsel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A legal subject is any subject that can be addressed by a legal case, law, bill, or other legal document or process.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all legal systems. This is the set of laws and the legal processes to create and implement those laws for a given sovereign.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legal System
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Use mso:location.location instead to represent the domain of a lawyer. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all pieces of legislation, i.e. laws that have been enacted by a legislature.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legislation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legislation to the date (if any) that the law is no longer effective.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legislation to the effective start date of the law.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.legislation to the mso:government.governmental_jurisdiction in which the law applies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Jurisdiction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all legislative buildings. These are the buildings that are the location for legislative activities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legislative Building

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A litigant is any party to a legal case.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Litigant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The case or cases this entity has been party to.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Party to cases

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or organization that specializes in helping clients resolve conflicts outside of the court system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mediation Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A public officer permitted by law to serve the public in non-contentious matters concerned with, for example, estates, deeds, powers-of-attorney, and foreign and international business.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notary

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all overturned convictions. These are convictions which were later nullified, either because the defendant was exonerated or for some other reason.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Overturned Conviction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.overturned_conviction to the amount of compensation awarded to the person wrongly convicted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compensation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.overturned_conviction to the number of years the wrongly convicted person spent in prison.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Years Imprisoned

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or organization that assists lawyers in legal work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Paralegal Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The primary entity representing the collection of all patents. Patents are the legal constructs that give an inventor sole rights to an invention.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent to its abstract. Patent applications and grants include both an abstract and a specification. Specification data should be mapped to type.object.description, and abstract data mapped to this property.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Abstract

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to patent kind code that was assigned to the patent when the patent was initially filed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Application Patent Kind Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the type of application of the patent, e.g. "utility application" and "provisional application".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Application Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.us_patent to the attorney or law firm associated with the patent application.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Attorney

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: roperty relating an mso:law.patent to its classification(s).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent to the country granting the patent to the invention.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the date that the patent was approved.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Issued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the date that the application for the patent was filed with the relevant patent office (indicated with the property law.patent.patent_office).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of Application

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the date on which the application draft of the patent was complete.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Produced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the date that the content of the patent was broadly disseminated, if this was done before the patent was issued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Published

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent to the mso:law.patent_examiner_relationship, which collects the data on the patent's examiners.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Examiner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.us_patent to the filing date for the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Filing Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the corresponding category of the International Patent Classification (IPC) system, e.g. C21 "Metallurgy of Iron".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: International Patent Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to an invention covered by the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Invention

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the language in which the patent is written.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent to the number of claims within the patent. Claims define the limits of the patent does and does not cover.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Claims

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the patent office where the application for the patent was filed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Office

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.us_patent to its prior publication date.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prior Publication Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent to any priority claims included in a patent document. Priority claims relate subsequent patent filings to a previous one in another country.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Priority Claim

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to patent kind code that was assigned to the patent when the patent was first published.
Property relating an mso:law.patent to the mso:law.patent_citation referenced in the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reference Cited
Patent Assignee
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Use event.agent instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:event.agent]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: patents_assigned
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. If this property is needed, it should be added to event.agent. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting data on the citation a patent references. Data for the patent citation includes the document, the category of the citation, and its citation number, with regard to the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Citation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_citation to its category and usually indicates which agent added the citation, either the examiner or the applicant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_citation to the document referenced in the citation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Document

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_citation to its number in the patent document.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all patent classification systems. These are the systems that allow examiners of patents to code documents by their technical features. The International Patent Classification (IPC) is an agreed international system, but there are others, as well as national and enterprise-specific patent classification systems.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on a patent's classification. Any given patent may have multiple classifications by different classification systems. This type is further subtyped into two kinds of relationships: mso:law.broad_patent_classification_relationship and mso:law.detailed_patent_classification_relationship. mso:law.broad_patent_classification_relationship is a relationship that captures the general properties of a patent classification, like 'main classification'. mso:law.detailed_patent_classification_relationship provides many more properties to give a detailed description of the patent's classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_classification_relationship to the system of classification used in this classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_classification_relationship to the edition or version of the classification system used in this classification of the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Version

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data for an examiner on a given patent. Includes the examiner, their role, and department.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Examiner Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_examiner_relationship to the department of the examiner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Department

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_examiner_relationship to one of the people examining the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.patent_examiner_relationship to the role the given examiner has. For example, primary examiner, assistant examiner, or authorized officer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Role

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that contains properties to specify the codes and code descriptions used by patent offices across the world, e.g. A2 is a code used by Argentina to indicate a divisional patent application.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Kind Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the code itself, e.g. "A1", "B2", "E", etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Code

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the sovereign that uses the corresponding patent code (indicated with the property law.patent_kind_code.code).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sovereign

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A governmental or intergovernmental agency that issues patents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Office
patents
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The property on which this virtual property is based has been deprecated. If this property is needed, a new virtual property should be created, based on law.patent.patent_office. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An attorney that specializes in cases resulting in injury or death, particularly workplace or traffic accidents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Personal Injury Attorney

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all police departments. Police departments are law enforcement organizations with local jurisdiction that, among other things, make arrests, protect property, and limit civil disorder.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Police Department

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on priority claims in patents. Data includes the country, prior patent, office of filing, and kind of priority claim.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Priority Claim

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.priority_claim to the mso:location.country the first application was filed in.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.priority_claim to the kind of claim: national, regional, or international.
Property relating an mso:law.priority_claim to the the mso:law.patent that is the first application of the patent, but in a different country.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prior Patent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies, in the form of a number, the precedence of the given priority claim.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sequence

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all pieces of proposed legislation, i.e. bills that are under consideration for enactment or state or local government initiatives that are held for a vote.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Proposed Legislation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a proposed legislation to an action that was taken with respect to the legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Actions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a piece of proposed legislation to information about the number of members of a political party who voted a particular way with respect to this proposed legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aggregated Vote

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a proposed legislation to a cosponsor of the legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cosponsors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a proposed legislation to a unique identifier for the legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a proposed legislation to the date/time when the legislation was first proposed for a vote in a legislative house.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a proposed legislation to the legislative session where the bill was introduced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legislative Session

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a proposed legislation to a vote that was cast in a legislative house for the legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Legislative Votes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a proposed legislation to a politician who is a sponsor of the legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sponsors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a proposed legislation to the current status of the legislation in the process of its becoming law.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a piece of proposed legislation to a politician who voted on the legislation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Voters

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all robberies. Robberies are crimes in which an agent takes or attempts to take something of value by force or threat of force.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Robbery

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.robbery to the mso:business.asset that was stolen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stolen

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.robbery to the dated money value of the goods stolen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Value of Stole Goods

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity containing groupings of sentences, such as 'prison' and 'capital punishment'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sentence Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The primary entity representing the collection of all U.S. patents. These are the United States legal constructs that give an inventor sole rights to an invention.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the date that the application for the patent was filed with the US Patent and Trademark Office.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Application Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the number that was assigned to the patent application by the US Patent and Trademark Office.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Application Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the date (if any) that the patent was revoked.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Revoked

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:law.us_patent to the broadest claims in the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Exemplary Claim

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to the corresponding category of the International Patent Classification (IPC) system, e.g. C21 "Metallurgy of Iron".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: International Patent Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to an invention covered by the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Invention

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a patent to an inventor whose invention is covered by the patent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inventor
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use the following path instead: law.patent.invention -> law.invention.inventor. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:law.invention.inventor]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the date that the patent was approved.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Issue Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the agent to which the patent rights are assigned, if this is someone other than the inventor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Assignee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to the final number that was assigned to the patent by the US Patent and Trademark Office if the patent was approved.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The patent office this patent application was filed with.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Patent office
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to law.patent, since the expected type includes all international patent offices. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to a category in one of the two classification systems recognized by the US Patent and Trademark Office, viz. the US Patent Classification (USPC) and the Cooperative Patent Classification (CPC).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: US Patent Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a US patent to one of the six types of patents recognized by the US Patent and Trademark Office, viz. utility patent, design patent, plant patent, reissue patent, defensive publication (DEF), and statutory invention registration (SIR).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: US Patent Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing the categories of the two classification systems recognized by the US Patent and Trademark Office, viz. the US Patent Classification (USPC) and the Cooperative Patent Classification (CPC).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: US Patent Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the six types of patents recognized by the US Patent and Trademark Office, viz. utility patent, design patent, plant patent, reissue patent, defensive publication (DEF), and statutory invention registration (SIR).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: US Patent Type
